h3. Issue Summary
When using bullet points on the new editor *with* a colored text will add new lines before and after the word with the color format

h3. Environment
* Cloud

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # On the new issue view, add the following text and click on save:
{code}* a {color:#00b8d9}*b*{color}{code}
# Refresh the page

h3. Expected Results
Jira should keep the colored word in the same line

h3. Actual Results
Jira adds a new line before and after the color format

The below data was found on the database for the same text provided before:

description:
{code}* a {color:#00b8d9}*b*{color}{code}
escription_adf
{noformat}
{
    "content": [
        {
            "content": [
                {
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "a ",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                        },
                        {
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "marks": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "strong"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "attrs": {
                                                "color": "#00b8d9"
                                            },
                                            "type": "textColor"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "text": "b",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                        }
                    ],
                    "type": "listItem"
                }
            ],
            "type": "bulletList"
        }
    ],
    "type": "doc",
    "version": 1
}

{noformat}
h3. Notes

h3. Workaround

No workaround was found.

h3. Issue Summary

As part of the [efforts to remove username|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/blog/2018/06/say-goodbye-to-usernames-in-atlassian-cloud] in cloud, some users are already configured with a UUID as the username. When those users are referenced in a JQL query (assignee/reporter), the data user information is not readable.

ie. 
{code}
assignee in (<UUID1>, <UUID2>)
{code}


h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Go to Jira search (advanced)
 # Build a JQL referencing to existing users that has UUID as a username.
 # Check the JQL that was generated. 

h3. Expected Results

The JQL should reference to a readable user information. 

ie. 

{code}
assignee in (<email_address1>, <email_address2>)
{code}

{code}
assignee in (<display_name1>, <display_name2>)
{code}


h3. Actual Results

{code}
assignee in (<UUID1>, <UUID2>)
{code}


h3. Workaround

- Run the JQL in Jira search and switch to *Basic* to retrieve the user information. 
- Run the JQL query and inspect the results to check for the user information.
